# Console command renderers

## Commands (`*Command.php`)

- Handle `configure()`, read `InputInterface`, call facades/use cases, compute **exit code** in the command (`Command::SUCCESS` / `Command::FAILURE`).
- Do **not** embed large formatted output, ASCII trees, or table layouts in the command class.
- **Orchestration-only** messages are allowed in the command (e.g. a single `<error>` line when a facade call fails), matching [ListCapabilitiesCommand](src/Capability/CapabilityListing/Presentation/CommandLine/Command/ListCapabilitiesCommand.php).

## Renderers (`Command/Renderer/*Renderer.php`)

- Place under `Presentation/CommandLine/Command/Renderer/`.
- Use `final readonly class`, constructor has no side effects.
- **One responsibility:** format and write CLI output.
- Prefer **`OutputInterface`** with `$output->writeln()` / `$output->write()` and Console tags; use `Symfony\Component\Console\Helper\Table` for tables.
- Avoid `SymfonyStyle` in new renderers unless there is a strong reason; keep parity with [ListCapabilitiesRenderer](src/Capability/CapabilityListing/Presentation/CommandLine/Command/Renderer/ListCapabilitiesRenderer.php).

## Headers

- New PHP files in this area MUST include the standard proprietary license header per [copyright-notice.mdc](copyright-notice.mdc).

## Example (command delegates output)

```php
$this->renderer->renderSummary($output, $summary);
```
